==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smear
<hw>Smear</hw> <pr>(sm⟦emac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Smeared</conjf> <pr>(sm⟦emac⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Smearing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>smeren</ets>, <ets>smerien</ets>, AS. <ets>smierwan</ets>,
<ets>smyrwan</ets>, fr. <ets>smeoru</ets> fat, grease; akin to D.
<ets>smeren</ets>, OHG. <ets>smirwen</ets>, G. <ets>schmieren</ets>,
Icel. <ets>smyrja</ets> to anoint. See <er>Smear</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To overspread with anything
unctuous, viscous, or adhesive; to daub; <as>as, to <ex>smear</ex>
anything with oil</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Smear</xex> the sleepy grooms
with blood.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To soil in any way; to contaminate; to pollute; to
stain morally; <as>as, to be <ex>smeared</ex> with infamy</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To smudge, blur, or render indistinct (writing,
pictures, etc.).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>to vilify (a person); to damage (a person's
reputation), especially falsely or by unfair innuendo, and with
malicious intent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smear</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Smear
<hw>Smear</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>smere</ets>,.
<ets>smeoru</ets> fat, grease; akin to D. <ets>smeer</ets>, G.
<ets>schmeer</ets>, OHG. <ets>smero</ets>, Icel. <ets>smj⟦oum⟧r</ets>,
Sw. & Dan. <ets>sm⟦oum⟧r</ets> butter, Goth.
<ets>sma⟦iacute⟧r⟦thorn⟧r</ets> fatness, <ets>smarna</ets> dung; cf.
Lith. <ets>smarsas</ets> fat. Cf. <er>Smirch</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A fat, oily substance; oinment.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a spot made by, or as by, an unctuous or
adhesive substance; a blot or blotch; a daub; a stain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Slow broke the morn,⟦br⟧
All damp and rolling vapor, with no sun,⟦br⟧
But in its place a moving <qex>smear</qex> of light.</q>
<rj><qau>Alexander Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smearcase</ent>⟦br⟧
